    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357\">\n<html><head>\n \n</head> \n\n \n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">In case Exception is mentioned \nin the throws clause of method you may try something like this \n</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">try </font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">{</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font size=\"2\">method with \ninput that causes the expected Exception to be thrown.</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \nassert(false);</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">}</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">catch (ExpectedException \ne)</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">{</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font\n size=\"2\">assert(true);</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">}</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">in case the the exception \nthrown is not mentioned either in throws clause or the documentation,&nbsp; it \nshould be treated as a bug/bad programming.</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">It does not matter whether the \nexception is system level or user defined.</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">Hope it \nhelps,</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">Sachin</font></span></div>\n<blockquote><span title=\"qreply\"> <blockquote dir=\"ltr\" style=\"MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;\">\n  <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357OutlookMessageHeader\" dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"\n size=\"2\">-----Original Message-----<br><b>From:</b> G Ramasubramani \n  [mailto:grama@...]<br><b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, December 19, 2000 1:45 \n  PM<br><b>To:</b> junit@egroups.com<br><b>Subject:</b> [junit] Exception \n  Handling Question<br><br></font></div>\n  <table id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357INCREDIMAINTABLE\" cellSpacing=\"0\" cellPadding=\"2\" width=\"100%\"\n border=\"0\"><tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357INCREDIHEADER\" width=\"100%\"></td></tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357INCREDITEXTREGION\" style=\"DIRECTION:ltr;\" width=\"100%\">\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>Hi,</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In case I have a method which \n        throws an exception on a particular input, what would be the best way to \n        write a test case which shall succeed in case the exception is \n        thrown?</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I thought of using something \n        like </div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; try {</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; object.method();</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;catch(ExpectedExceptionName \n        e) {</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n        &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; assert(&quot;expected message&quot;, e.getMessage());</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In this case however, it is a \n        user defined exception and hence I know what message to expect. What \n        would be a proper course of action in case it is a system level \n        exception?</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I searched the archives, but \n        could not find any mention of this.</div>\n        <div>&nbsp;</div>\n        <div>thanks,</div>\n        <div>Rama</div></td></tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357INCREDIFOOTER\" width=\"100%\">\n        <table cellSpacing=\"0\" cellPadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\">\n          <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td width=\"100%\"></td>\n            <td id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357INCREDISOUND\" vAlign=\"bottom\" align=\"middle\"></td>\n            <td id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357INCREDIANIM\" vAlign=\"bottom\"\n align=\"middle\"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><span\n id=\"ygrps-yiv-1115930357IncrediStamp\">\n  <p align=\"left\"><font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"\n size=\"2\">__________________________________________________<br><font\n face=\"Comic Sans MS\" size=\"2\"><i>IncrediMail</i> - <b>Email has finally \n  evolved</b> - </font><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.incredimail.com/imstamp26.html\"><font\n face=\"Times New Roman\" size=\"3\"><b><u>Click \